RIP Grandpa.  Elmer Lewis was one of a kind. Barely talked when my brother and I were kids. In his later years, he became the life of the party, especially at shows. If you happened to be near my grandparents, there was a good chance you’d be getting one of my guitar picks.  They would promote the band everywhere they went. You’ll be missed, Grandpa. 🤘🤘

The era-defining hit ‘Last Resort’ could have sounded SO different…

My guest on @thedownbeat podcast this week is Jerry Horton (@jerryhorton), guitarist and founding member of the hugely successful rock band Papa Roach. We talk about their pivotal role in creating what is now known as ’Nu Metal’ and their resilience to the genre‘s somewhat bad connotations that has seen them remain successful and relevant for 30 (THIRTY) years. We talk about their song writing process and also about our love of CARS, PRIMUS, METALLICA, and much more. Available in 4K on YT or audio wherever you cast your pods.
Husband, father, guitarist for Papa Roach, car nut, and photographer. If you like cars, follow me at @drivekulture
